2026-05-28 | Vertical Sum of Binary Tree

	Question
Return vertical sums of binary tree.
	Key Insight
Assign every node a:
		horizontal distance (HD)
Rules:
- root → HD = 0
- left child → HD - 1
- right child → HD + 1
Nodes having same HD
belong to same vertical line.
	Approach
1.	Use DFS traversal  
2.	Pass current horizontal distance  
3.	Store:
		sum for each HD
		in ordered map
4.	Traverse:
		left with hd-1
		right with hd+1
5.	Finally:
		extract sums from ordered map
	Time Complexity
	O(n log n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    void dfs(Node* root,
             int hd,
             map<int,int>& mp){
        if(root == NULL)
            return;
        mp[hd] += root->data;
        dfs(root->left, hd - 1, mp);
        dfs(root->right, hd + 1, mp);
    }
    vector<int> verticalSum(Node *root) {
        map<int,int> mp;
        dfs(root, 0, mp);
        vector<int> ans;
        for(auto &it : mp){
            ans.push_back(it.second);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Horizontal distance uniquely identifies
a vertical line in the tree.  
So the problem becomes:
		group nodes by HD
		and sum them.
